==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*wurti-''.  Cognate with Old Saxon [[wurt]], Old High German [[wurz]] (German [[Wurz]]), Old Norse [[urt]] (Swedish [[ört]]), Gothic [[𐍅𐌰𐌿𐍂𐍄𐍃]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /wyrt/

===Noun===
'''wyrt''' ''f''
# a [[plant]] or [[herb]], especially as used for food or medicine

